  "text": "Groups of 5-10 mice were infected intraperitoneally with 5 · 10 2 or 5 · 10 3 blood-form trypomastigotes of the Tulahuem strain of T. cruzi in 0Á2 ml of 0Á15 M phosphate-buffered saline (PBS). Control mice received the same volume of PBS. The numbers of parasites were evaluated in 5 ll of blood, as previously described. [CITATION_1] In vitro cell culture Splenocytes were cultured in triplicates at a density of 10 7 cells/well in 24-well plates (Nunc, Roskilde, Denmark) in RPMI-1640 (Gibco, Grand Island, NY) supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS, Hyclone, South Logan, UT), 50 mM 2-mercaptoethanol and 1 mM HEPES (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO). Cells were cultured at 37°and 5% of CO 2 for 48 hr in complete medium alone. Supernatants were kept at )70°until further experiments.",
